-- Cattle Prices Drop as Holiday Beef Demand Slows; Hogs Decline
-- B y   E l i z a b e t h   C a m p b e l l
-- 2013-07-02T15:31:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-02/cattle-prices-drop-as-holiday-beef-demand-slows-hogs-decline.html
Cattle futures slumped on signs that
U.S. grocers have finished buying beef for the Fourth of July
holiday. Hog prices also fell.  Meatpackers have a shortened-slaughter week with the
federal holiday and processed 123,000 cattle yesterday, down 3.9
percent from a year earlier, government data show.  Independence
Day  on July 4 is the most-popular day for outdoor grilling,
according to the Hearth, Patio and Barbecue Association.  “Our immediate needs are met,” Lawrence Kane, a senior
market adviser at Stewart-Peterson Group, said in a telephone
interview from  Yates City ,  Illinois . “The whole meat industry
always gets out of whack over holidays.”  Cattle futures for August delivery fell 0.3 percent to
$1.2185 a pound at 10:28 a.m. on the Chicago Mercantile
Exchange. Prices were down 7.7 percent this year through
yesterday.  Feeder-cattle futures for August settlement dropped 0.3
percent to $1.50825 a pound.  Hog futures for August settlement retreated 0.5 percent to
96.475 cents a pound on the CME. The commodity is up 13 percent
this year through yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
